    "content": "**Geopolitiks Snacks** - May 11, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🛢️ Iran answered the peace plan with a ransom note\n\nThe Gulf ceasefire talks have reached the delicate phase where both sides describe the other proposal as surrender. Efficient diplomacy.\n\n- **The rejection:** AP reports Iran responded to the latest U.S. proposal on Sunday, while Trump called the answer unacceptable.\n- **The demands:** Iranian state TV said Tehran wanted war reparations, full sovereignty over the Strait of Hormuz, sanctions relief and the release of frozen assets.\n- **The market signal:** Reuters reported oil prices jumped Monday as the rejection raised fears the 10-week war will keep Hormuz shipping paralyzed.\n\n*The ceasefire remains alive in the same way a smoke alarm remains a kitchen appliance.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/f8812db41837336d816efaea7bc1c44a) | [Reuters via WIN 98.5](https://wincountry.com/2026/05/10/trump-rejects-irans-response-to-us-peace-proposal-as-unacceptable/)\n\n---\n\n## ⚓ Manila and Tokyo found another China-shaped procurement form\n\nThe South China Sea is doing what it does best: turning diplomatic alarm into naval shopping lists.\n\n- **The pact:** AP says Japan and the Philippines agreed to start talks on a weapons transfer arrangement that could let Tokyo provide used destroyers to Manila.\n- **The trigger:** both defense chiefs cited China's intensifying coercive actions in disputed waters.\n- **The second file:** Reuters says the Philippine Coast Guard accused a Chinese vessel of illegal marine research near the gas-rich Reed Bank inside Manila's exclusive economic zone.\n\n*Nothing calms a maritime dispute like adding destroyers to the minutes.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/3c337bba04f0079278eff1436f177ad5) | [Reuters via WKZO](https://wkzo.com/2026/05/07/philippines-says-china-vessel-conducting-illegal-research-near-gas-rich-reed-bank/)\n\n---\n\n## 🛰️ Sudan turned a drone strike into a regional accusation\n\nKhartoum's war was already catastrophic; now it has added another neighbor to the blame map.\n\n- **The attack:** AP says Sudanese air defenses shot down a drone approaching Khartoum's main airport on May 4, with no casualties or damage reported.\n- **The accusation:** the military-aligned government then blamed Ethiopia for recent drone attacks and recalled its ambassador from Addis Ababa.\n- **The context:** Sudan's army and the Rapid Support Forces have been at war since April 2023, with the country already pushed toward famine and state collapse.\n\n*The conflict needed less regionalization. Naturally, it got diplomatic escalation instead.*\n\n**Sources:** [AP](https://apnews.com/article/bc6346acd2f99586e1ffbe188ddfc896) | [AP](https://apnews.com/article/907855de58f8c5ad89a1cd92897e5749)\n"
  }
]
